This paper is about language modeling using a specific type of neural network architecture, the Highway LSTM. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses experimental results and compares different types of HW-LSTM, which suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model architecture, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering), as it involves designing and implementing a new software system. The use of neural networks also suggests that it may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with the development and application of neural networks and other biologically-inspired algorithms. Finally, the paper's focus on improving speech recognition accuracy suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems.
